  <mainDescription>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Purpose&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    This metric is used to help the team understand the stability of their requirements.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Definition&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Count: total number of requirements in each&amp;nbsp;stability category&amp;nbsp;(e.g.&amp;nbsp;High, Medium, Low)&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Group by requirement type (e.g. Feature, Supplementary, Use Case)&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Analysis&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Look for a reasonable distribution across all stability categories. Too many low-stability requirements can indicate a&#xD;
    problem with the quality of the requirements.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Below is an example of a Requirements Distribution by&amp;nbsp;Stability report, which shows the number of requirements by&#xD;
    stability.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &lt;img alt=&quot;Requirements Distribution by Stability report&quot; src=&quot;./resources/rqmt_distr_by_stability.gif&quot; width=&quot;600&quot;&#xD;
    height=&quot;307&quot; />&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Collection and reporting tools&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    IBM&amp;reg; Rational&amp;reg; Requirements Composer&amp;reg; and&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;IBM&amp;reg; Rational&amp;reg; DOORS&amp;reg; collect Requirements&amp;nbsp;stability&#xD;
    data.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;IBM&amp;reg; Rational&amp;reg; Insight&amp;reg; reports on this metric.&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
